The paper deals with the problem of incomplete networks and proposes an algorithm to increase the size of the observed network. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistical learning (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as community discovery and influence maximization, which are relevant to the sub-category of social computing (cs.SOC).
